## 5. HTTP and WebSocket APIs

### HTTP API Endpoints (REST)

All HTTP routes are prefixed with `/api` to route through ingress load balancers.

#### 1. Authentication
*   `POST /api/auth/signup`: Registers a new user. Enforces strict field requirements (valid email structure, password length ≥ 6, unique username).
*   `POST /api/auth/login`: Authenticates a user and returns a JWT token.
*   `GET /api/auth/me`: Refreshes the user profile and fetches the latest status.

#### 2. Payments
*   `GET /api/payment/config`: Returns the active Razorpay API key ID and details about mock payment settings.
*   `POST /api/payment/order`: Authenticates the user and opens a transaction order on Razorpay for ₹25 (2500 paise).
*   `POST /api/payment/verify`: Cryptographically validates the Razorpay checkout signature.

#### 3. General
*   `GET /api/languages`: Returns the list of supported languages.
*   `GET /api/terms`: Serves the terms of service.
*   `GET /api/credits`: Serves the credits page.

### WebSocket Socket.io Packets (`id` Map)

WS events communicate over the multiplexed `data` channel with a payload format of `{ id: Number, data: Any }`.

#### Client-to-Server
*   `id: 6`: Report player (toxic, spam, botting).
*   `id: 7`: Mute player.
*   `id: 8`: Rate drawing (like/dislike).
*   `id: 9`: Custom avatar sync.
*   `id: 12`: Owner settings modification.
*   `id: 18`: Select word from choices.
*   `id: 19`: Real-time drawing commands (batched arrays).
*   `id: 20`: Clear canvas.
*   `id: 21`: Undo canvas command.
*   `id: 30`: Submit chat message/guess.

#### Server-to-Client
*   `id: 1`: Broadcast player join.
*   `id: 2`: Broadcast player exit.
*   `id: 5`: Broadcast votekick update.
*   `id: 8`: Broadcast rating statistics.
*   `id: 9`: Broadcast avatar update.
*   `id: 10`: Initialize lobby details.
*   `id: 11`: Broadcast game state transition.
*   `id: 12`: Broadcast setting updates.
*   `id: 13`: Send word hint letters.
*   `id: 14`: Sync countdown clock.
*   `id: 15`: Broadcast player guessed correctly.
*   `id: 16`: Notify guess is close (Levenshtein distance alert).
*   `id: 17`: Broadcast lobby ownership transfer.
*   `id: 19`: Sync real-time canvas paths.
*   `id: 20`: Clear canvas.
*   `id: 21`: Sync canvas undo.
*   `id: 30`: Sync chat feed messages.
*   `id: 32`: private warning for chat spam.

